# Runbook — Ops & Troubleshooting

## Quick Health Check

```bash
/auto-status     # DLQ depth, token budget, rate limit usage
/auto-doctor     # Infrastructure health check
```

## Common Failures

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
|---------|-------|-----|
| `429 Too Many Requests` | LLM rate limit | Auto-retries (3x). Check token budget if persistent. |
| ADO API 401 | Token expired | Pipeline: re-run. Lambda: rotate `ADO_PAT` in env vars. |
| `Token budget exhausted` | Monthly cap hit | Wait for month rollover or increase `MONTHLY_TOKEN_CAP`. |
| `rate limit exceeded` | Daily cap hit | Resets at midnight UTC. Adjust in `rate-limiter.js`. |
| `scanner: degraded mode` | Content Safety down | Fail-open — pipelines continue with local detection. |
| Plugin install failure | Pipeline variables wrong | Check `ADO_ORG_URL` and `DX_MARKETPLACE_URL`. |
| Delegation failed | Pipeline map wrong | Check `CROSS_REPO_PIPELINE_MAP` JSON. |
| Webhooks stopped | Auto-disabled by ADO | Re-enable in Service Hooks settings. |

## Investigating a Failed Run

1. **Find the run** — ADO > Pipelines > select pipeline > recent runs
2. **Check the bundle** — S3 bucket: `run.json`, `decision-journal.json`, `alerts.json`
3. **Check DLQ** — `node .ai/automation/eval/process-dlq.js`

## Quick Rollback

| What | How |
|------|-----|
| Bad prompt | `git revert <commit>`, push, eval validates automatically |
| Bad Lambda | `aws lambda list-versions-by-function`, roll back via `aws_lambda_deploy` |
| Disable one agent | Remove its `TAG_GATE_*` env var from WI Router Lambda |
| Disable all agents | Disable WI service hooks in ADO, or set rate limit to 0 |

## Maintenance

- **Weekly**: `/auto-status`, run eval (`node .ai/automation/eval/run.js --all`)
- **Monthly**: Review token budget, check DLQ empty, rotate ADO PAT if expiring

